    "Examples of LLM generations across various pivots are presented in Appendix D.",
    "After these generations and labels are generated, we analyze them to identify bias in two layers:",
    "Choice Refusal Percentage (CRP): CRP denotes the percentage of generations where the model understood that a choice itself is harmful and rejected to make a choice in the task.",
    "Stereotype Polarity is the percentage of positive stereotypes chosen.",
    "It is computed over the samples where a choice was made."
